                        <p>Cyber incidents in U.S. schools have reached 1,331 since 2016, with 33% of these incidents involving breaches of student data.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card">
                        <h3>Commercial Exploitation</h3>
                        <p>Nearly 90% of educational platforms collected and shared user data with advertising companies, exposing children to privacy violations.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h3>FERPA Implementation Challenges</h3>
                <p>The main issue is not that the law is broken, but rather that its flexibility is poorly understood and executed, resulting in confusion and risk-averse behaviour.</p>
                
                <h3>COPPA Limitations</h3>
                <p>COPPA is criticized for its lax enforcement, typically settling cases for amounts that are "slaps on the wrist" for large tech companies rather than meaningful deterrents.</p>
